picID=1016.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   PoP Pets Equipping Shields</span><hr size=1> <br>
I noticed recently that when I gave an elemental defender to my 61 air pet, the shield graphic did not show up.  This got me curious and so I did a little testing.<br>
<br>
I gave 61 air an elemental defender only and sent him in to battle.  The shield graphic was not there and he was dual wielding left and right.  I summoned up a new pet and gave him a mantle, an elemental blanket, and then an elemental defender (in that order).  Same results: pet would not wear shield and continued to dual wield.<br>
<br>
I tried GVoc earth and air and they both showed shield graphic and did not dual wield, as usual.<br>
<br>
So what does this mean?  Is it possible that PoP pets are summoned with certain equipment (a la epic armor), and  whatever is in secondary is better than an elemental defender?  Or are they just smart enough to know better than to equip a shield in secondary?  <br>
<br>
Shanuk Dandiprat<br>
Arch Mage of Drinal<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heofmanyfals>HeOfManyFals</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:19:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pets and shields</span><hr size=1> I've seen this even on lower level pets.<br>
<br>
My speculation is this.  We know that pets will automatically equip the weapon with the lowest delay that we give them.  The inherent delay of a dual-wielding pet is obviously lower than a shield, thus the pet never equips a shield in it's secondary slot.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shanukdandiprat>ShanukDandiprat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:22:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets and shields</span><hr size=1> <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The inherent delay of a dual-wielding pet is obviously lower than a shield, thus the pet never equips a shield <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Every non-PoP pet will equip a shield in secondary if it doesn't have any weapons, dual-wielding or not.  That is why you have to give the pet weapons after giving it an elemental defender to get it to dual wield.  I tested GVoc earth and air just to make sure that was still the case and it is.<br>
<br>
Shanuk Dandiprat<br>
Arch Mage of Drinal<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1323<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:25:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets and shields</span><hr size=1> A while back, there was a trick people used to do to de-dual wield mobs, and that was handing the mobs a 2h weapon. They'd wield it, and lose the ability to dual wield, dropping their DPS. Can't do that anymore, with a change that prevents dual wielding creatures from equipping 2h weapons. This inability to wield a shield may be a stem off of this, a block on equipping an item to keep the creature from losing the ability to dual wield innately.<br>
<br>
Edit: Of course, it may just be you. Me, I can't get the shield graphics to show up for even the elementalkin pets, and it couldn't dual wield if I begged it. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~c.wroten/graphics/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A> at: 2/26/03 8:26:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heofmanyfals>HeOfManyFals</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:45:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pets and Shields</span><hr size=1> Shanuk,<br>
<br>
<br>
How long ago did you test this?<br>
<br>
As of three weeks ago, I was unable to get a 44 pet to equip a shield at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=booperbustle>Booperbustle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 8:49:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets and Shields</span><hr size=1> If you're giving the shield to the pet after giving him other weapons, he's most likely throwing it into his &quot;back&quot; slot.  Notice elemental defenders can be worn secondary OR back slot.  Pets inherently are coded to place items in slots where it will be most beneficial to them.  When the pets get dual wield I'm guessing they decide to always default the shield to the back slot (even my 51+ pets didn't used to do this, maybe changed in a patch).  This preserves their quad hitting while still giving them the benefits of the stats on the item.  <br>
<br>
If you want to further test this try giving a naked pet a dropped shield that is secondary only.  If he equips it, my theory is correct.  If not, maybe he just ignores the shield as it would hamper his ability to dish out damage :-) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062">Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
