 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 471<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 11:48:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets and Shields</span><hr size=1> Pets are generally pretty good about showing you the shield they've equipped.  Try giving something other than the elemental defender... like a round shield from a skellie or something.  It's a lot more noticeable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tevzia>TevZia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 12:05:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets and Shields</span><hr size=1> An Elemental Defender isn't *That* hard to see.<br>
<br>
I'll try to remember to experiment a little tomorrow.. Giving a pet 2 Ele defenders at once should force it to equip it in both Back and 2nd.. <br>
<br>
I don't remeber if it's LORE or not so giving the pet 2 at once might be impossible. Pets ignore LORE tag though so it should equip both. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=halazar>Halazar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/03 12:52:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1016.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets and Shields</span><hr size=1> This is why we need some kind of interface to either:<br>
<br>
1) show us exactly what the pet has equiped where via a window just like any other inspection window (right click pet to inspect).<br>
<br>
